race.comment: OUR LITTLE STAR (4) win record hardly excites but comes here in peak condition. Stalked the fast tempo with a gritty second over 1200m at Cowra. Can get cover from the sticky draw and finish over the top of them. SHUTTERING (9) was a month between runs when she knocked up late to run sixth over 1200m at Wagga. Has further improvement and expected to go close in this easier race. SHEZAIN (7) returned from a lengthy break with a hard fought Maiden win over 1010m at Moruya. Finds a tougher test from the draw and expected to get the 1200m. Keep safe. LIAMENA AVENUE (8) kept fresh when he pushed forward for a fighting third over this trip at Moruya. On the quick backup and stays in the calculations. JAZZ ALL KNIGHT (3) has a good record over this track and trip and no surprise to see him bounce back in this class.
